@page "/guides/how-to-save-1-million-naira"
@using SmartBudget.Components.Pages.Blog
@attribute [AllowAnonymous]
@inherits BlogPostBase

<PageTitle>SmartBudget - How to Save ₦1,000,000 in One Year</PageTitle>

<link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/blog.css" />

<div class="blog-post-page">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="breadcrumb-container">
            <nav aria-label="Breadcrumb">
                <ol class="breadcrumb">
                    <li class="breadcrumb-item"><a href="/"><i class="bi bi-house-door"></i> Home</a></li>
                    <li class="breadcrumb-item"><i class="bi bi-chevron-right"></i></li>
                    <li class="breadcrumb-item"><a href="/guides">Guides</a></li>
                    <li class="breadcrumb-item"><i class="bi bi-chevron-right"></i></li>
                    <li class="breadcrumb-item active">How to Save ₦1,000,000</li>
                </ol>
            </nav>
        </div>

        <article class="blog-post">
            <div class="post-header">
                <span class="post-category-badge">Saving</span>
                <h1>How to Save ₦1,000,000 in One Year</h1>
                <div class="post-meta">
                    <span><i class="bi bi-person-circle"></i> SmartBudget Team</span>
                    <span><i class="bi bi-calendar3"></i> @CurrentDate</span>
                    <span><i class="bi bi-clock"></i> 15 min read</span>
                    <span><i class="bi bi-file-text"></i> Intermediate</span>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="post-body-content">
                <p>Saving ₦1,000,000 in one year is achievable with discipline and the right strategy. This guide shows you exactly how.</p>

                <h2>The Math</h2>
                <p>To save ₦1,000,000 in 12 months, you need to save:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Monthly:</strong> ₦83,333</li>
                    <li><strong>Weekly:</strong> ₦19,230</li>
                    <li><strong>Daily:</strong> ₦2,740</li>
                </ul>

                <h2>Step 1: Track Your Income and Expenses</h2>
                <p>Use SmartBudget to track every Naira you earn and spend. You'll be surprised how small expenses add up.</p>

                <h2>Step 2: Create a Realistic Budget</h2>
                <p>Follow the 50/30/20 rule adapted for Nigerians:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>50% Needs:</strong> Rent, food, utilities, transportation</li>
                    <li><strong>30% Wants:</strong> Entertainment, shopping, dining out</li>
                    <li><strong>20% Savings:</strong> Your ₦1,000,000 goal</li>
                </ul>

                <h2>Step 3: Cut Unnecessary Expenses</h2>
                <p>Review your spending and identify areas to cut:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Cook at home instead of eating out (save ₦30,000/month)</li>
                    <li>Use public transportation (save ₦20,000/month)</li>
                    <li>Cancel unused subscriptions (save ₦10,000/month)</li>
                    <li>Shop with a list (save ₦15,000/month)</li>
                </ul>

                <h2>Step 4: Increase Your Income</h2>
                <p>Consider these side hustles:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Freelancing (Graphic design, writing, programming)</li>
                    <li>Starting a small business</li>
                    <li>Investing in stocks or mutual funds</li>
                    <li>Offering consulting services</li>
                </ul>

                <h2>Step 5: Automate Your Savings</h2>
                <p>Set up automatic transfers to your savings account on payday. Save first, then spend what's left.</p>

                <h2>Step 6: Use SmartBudget's Goal Tracking</h2>
                <p>Set up your ₦1,000,000 goal in SmartBudget and track your progress daily.</p>

                <h2>Sample Monthly Savings Plan</h2>
                <div class="table-wrapper">
                    <table>
                        <thead>
                            <tr><th>Category</th><th>Amount (₦)</th></tr>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody>
                            <tr><td>Income from job</td><td>300,000</td></tr>
                            <tr><td>Side hustle income</td><td>50,000</td></tr>
                            <tr><td>Total Income</td><td>350,000</td></tr>
                            <tr><td>Needs (50%)</td><td>175,000</td></tr>
                            <tr><td>Wants (30%)</td><td>105,000</td></tr>
                            <tr><td>Savings (20%)</td><td>70,000</td></tr>
                            <tr><td>Additional savings from cutting expenses</td><td>13,333</td></tr>
                            <tr><td><strong>Total Monthly Savings</strong></td><td><strong>83,333</strong></td></tr>
                        </tbody>
                    </table>
                </div>

                <h2>Stay Motivated</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>Track your progress weekly</li>
                    <li>Celebrate small milestones</li>
                    <li>Visualize what ₦1,000,000 means for you</li>
                    <li>Join a savings accountability group</li>
                </ul>

                <div class="post-cta">
                    <h3>Start Saving Today</h3>
                    <p>Join thousands of Nigerians using SmartBudget to reach their savings goals.</p>
                    <a href="/Account/Register" class="btn-cta">Get Started Free →</a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </article>
    </div>
</div>

@code {
    protected override async Task OnInitializedAsync()
    {
        PageName = "guide-post";
        await base.OnInitializedAsync();
    }
}